      <head>Robert Kröner</head>
      <div>
        <p>German publisher, proprietor of the <ref cRef="entity-002405">J. G. Cotta'sche
            Buchhandlung Nachfolger</ref> (Successor(s) to J. G. Cotta's Book Dealership) from 1911
          to his death in 1945.</p>

        <p>The son of <ref cRef="entity-006260">Adolf von Kröner</ref>, he became an employee of his
          father's company, <ref cRef="entity-002405">J. G. Cotta'sche Buchhandlung Nachfolger</ref>
          in 1897, a partner in 1907 (see <ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-9-31_15">OJ 9/31,
            [15]</ref>), and sole proprietor after his father's death in 1911. Robert changed the
          firm to a public company in 1939. The firm's buildings were destroyed in 1943. Robert died
          in 1945; his son Adolf Robert Kröner, having served during World War II, became managing
          director in 1948.</p>
      </div>
